16 WHEREAS, rehabilitation services, including physical therapy and occupational therapy, are
17 essential for the long-term recovery and well-being of trauma survivors; and
18 WHEREAS, public education and awareness campaigns are necessary to inform the
19 community about the causes and consequences of physical trauma and the available
20 resources for support and recovery; and
21 WHEREAS, legislative support is needed to ensure adequate funding for trauma centers,
22 research into trauma treatment, and policies that enhance public safety; and
23 WHEREAS, community organizations and volunteers play a significant role in supporting
24 trauma survivors and promoting safety and prevention efforts.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body commend Georgia's trauma professionals, the Georgia Trauma
27 Commission, and the Georgia Trauma Foundation as well as recognize February 26, 2025,
28 as Trauma Awareness Day at the state capitol to raise awareness about physical trauma,
29 promote prevention and safety measures, support trauma care and rehabilitation services, and
30 honor the efforts of medical professionals, community organizations, and volunteers in
31 addressing physical trauma.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the
34 public and the press.
